3. cs.GT (Game Theory) is relevant as the paper introduces a game-theoretic solution to couple agents from complementary teams. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is relevant as the proposed method can be applied to robotic systems for task allocation. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper deals with a distributed system of agents and proposes a solution using market-based negotiation models.
